    "This entails comparing LLM-generated assessments with real-world data and consulting with human experts in the field to enhance the reliability and robustness of occupational evaluations.",
    "This prompts the pivotal question of how such machine-based social evaluations are employed in practice, and whether they influence policies or exert long-term effects on the social perceptions of occupations.",
    "With 100+ million users and over 1.5 billion monthly visits (Hu 2023), GPT-4 leverages social legitimacy and ethical positioning.",
    "It can serve as an important amplifier of occupational social opinions, including prestige and social value attached to certain jobs.",
    "While this can increase access to information, individuals from diverse backgrounds and roles will find themselves increasingly exposed to this 'technological construction of society'."
